definitions.definition: A payment made by a tenant at intervals in order to lease a property .
examples: I am asking £300 a week rent .

definitions.definition: A similar payment for the use of a product , equipment or a service .
( economics ) A profit from possession of a valuable right , as a restricted license to engage in a trade or business.
examples: A New York city taxicab license earns more than $10,000 a year in rent .

definitions.definition: An object for which rent is charged or paid.
( video games ) An amount of virtual currency paid by a player to preserve their character , inventory , etc. between gameplay sessions in a multi-user dungeon .
